<paragraph blockId="107.[189,1399,1049,1145]" pageId="107" pageNumber="108">Monoecious. Receptacle multicelled, consisting of a series of superposed cells forming the main axis which extends into the primary appendage without apparent discontinuity. Antheridia are corner cells of appendage.</paragraph>
